==English==

===Etymology===
from Spanish [[renegado]], from Medieval Latin [[renegatus]], perfect participle of [[renegare]], ''to deny''

===Noun===
'''renegade'''
# an outlaw or rebel
# Phil Costantino is a renegade
# Éric too
# And Ginger is no doubt
# But Richard smith is the most notorious renegade of all.
# Andy wants to be a renegade but he doesn't know how.